Portfolioalfia2016-12-23T15:08:13+00:00 
Current Portfolio
To date, iAnthus has invested in finance and management partnerships in 4 states, potentially comprising 8 licenses, 9 dispensaries and 4 cultivation facilities.
 grassrootsvermont.com
 mayflowermedicinals.com
 myorganix.com
 rgreenleaf.org
×
iAnthus has an investment in Grassroots Vermont.

Nonprofit organization licensed to cultivate and dispense medical marijuana in Vermont
One of four vertically integrated license holders state-wide
Only approved statewide delivery operator
Delivery program supports a state-wide patient base

Vermont Market Facts

625,000 people in Vermont with ~2,500 patients currently registered.
13 million tourists
Patient registration grew by 156% over two years1
If legalized in the 2017 legislative session, the adult-use market alone is estimated to add $100 million in annual sales by 20202
Past versions of Adult Use legalization bills favor current license holders with significant advantages

LEARN MORE
×
iAnthus has an investment in Reynolds Greenleaf & Associates:

Market-share leader with ~17% market share across New Mexico
Three cultivation and dispensary licenses and a production license

New Mexico Market Facts

2.6 million people in New Mexico with ~22,000 registered cannabis patients
2016 projected market size of $52.9 million1
Newly revised medical certification process will increase registered patients
Management companies can manage multiple licenses
Unlimited number of dispensary locations per license
Plant counts expanded from 150 to 450 per license

LEARN MORE 
×iAnthus has partnered with the nation’s leading cannabis regulatory law firm to apply for three medical cannabis licenses.

Seeking three licenses in high-population density areas 


Advanced to phase 2 of the 3-phase application


Secured compliant real estate for cultivation facility and three dispensary locations

Massachusetts Market Facts

6.7 million people in Massachusetts  


2016 projected medical cannabis market size $78.7 million


Recreational use legislation is on the ballot for 2016


Ballot initiative provides recreational licensing advantages to medical license holders

LEARN MORE



 
 
  
 
 














































