Advisors






Mr. Bankier is a veteran early stage investor in the food tech, media tech, and regulated cannabis industries.
LEARN MORE


Alain BankierAdvisor








×


Alain BankierAdvisor
Alain Bankier is a veteran early stage investor in the food tech, media tech, and regulated cannabis industries. He was the co-founder of the precursor of the New York Angels, one of the leading early stage investment groups in the US. Mr. Bankier co-founded the Saveur Food Group (SFG) to create, acquire and build branded food companies. In 2008, SFG was merged with The Manischewitz Company and Mr. Bankier became the Co-President of Manischewitz until 2013.  Prior to his career in the food industry, Mr. Bankier was a founder of an international boutique investment bank, which he sold to BNP Paribas in 1989 and where he remained as the Co-Head of Corporate Finance and Mergers and Acquisitions North Americas until 2001. Mr. Bankier received an MBA from the NYU Stern School of Business, and both B.S. and B.A. degrees from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania.









Dr. Boxer, a nationally renowned senior health policy advisor, was a finalist for US Surgeon General in both the Clinton and Bush administrations. He is a Visiting Professor of Urology and Visiting Scholar at UCLA.
LEARN MORE


Dr. Richard BoxerMedical Advisor








×


Dr. Richard BoxerMedical Advisor
Dr. Richard Boxer is a member of the iAnthus Board, and serves as an advisor on healthcare public policy, patient advocacy, and physician outreach. Dr. Boxer is currently Clinical Professor of Urology and Scholar at the David Geffen School of Medicine at UCLA, the University of Wisconsin School of Medicine and Public Health, and was formerly Professor of Clinical Urology at the University of Miami Medical Center. Dr. Boxer was a finalist for the position of Surgeon General of the United States in both the Bill Clinton and George W. Bush administrations, and worked in the Clinton White House in 1993. Dr. Boxer served on the National Cancer Advisory Board and the National Institute of Diabetes, Digestive and Kidney Diseases at the National Institute of Health. He is dedicated to the advancement of research and improvement in medical standards in the provision of medical cannabis to cancer and other patients. Dr. Boxer was a citizen delegate to the World Health Organization, and is a recipient of a Presidential Citation and a Cancer Research Award from the American Urological Association. Dr. Boxer graduated cum laude with a B.A.and an MD from the University of Wisconsin. Dr. Boxer has more than 75 publications in medical journals and has delivered 62 invited lectureships over his distinguished career.









Mr. Cohen is a nationally recognized expert in the large-scale, commercial cultivation of legal cannabis.
LEARN MORE


Adam CohenCultivation Advisor








×


Adam CohenCultivation Advisor
Mr. Cohen is a nationally recognized expert in the large-scale, commercial cultivation of legal cannabis. Adam co-founded and is the Managing Director of MJardin, the largest commercial cultivator of cannabis in the U.S. MJardin provides select cannabis businesses across the country with turnkey cultivation management services, including licensure support, facility design, systems implementation, and the day-to-day operational management required to produce premium cannabis in large-scale and professionally managed facilities. Prior to co-founding MJardin, Mr. Cohen co-founded and served as Managing Director and Chief Operating Officer of Brilla Group, an alternative asset private equity firm focused on the luxury hotel and resort asset class. Mr. Cohen graduated magna cum laude from the University of Colorado at Boulder and received his J.D. degree from the University of Colorado School of Law.









Ms. Ford is the Founder and Executive Director of Grassroots Vermont, one of the four licensed not-for-profit medical cannabis cultivators, manufacturers and dispensaries in Vermont.
LEARN MORE


Alex FordOperations Advisor








×


Alex FordOperations Advisor
Alex Ford is the Founder and Executive Director of Grassroots Vermont, one of the four licensed not-for-profit medical cannabis cultivators, manufacturers and dispensaries in the State of Vermont. Ms. Ford has used her extensive background in social work to create a patient-centric model of healthcare delivery for access to medical cannabis. She has led her not-for-profit’s efforts in patient education and hospital and physician outreach. Ms. Ford graduated from Bard College with a degree in psychology and has taken additional course work in family systems, cultural diversity and counseling.  Prior to her founding of Grassroots Vermont, Ms. Ford was a Case Manager for Rutland Mental Health where she worked for the SUCCESS Program with emotionally disturbed children in collaboration with the Rutland City Public Schools.  Ms. Ford has been active in the Rutland community and has served on the Educational Advisory Board at the Marble Valley Regional Correctional Facility.









Ms. Lewis, founder of the award-winning Mountain Medicine, is chair of the National Cannabis Industry Association and the founder and chair of the Cannabis Business Alliance.
LEARN MORE


Jaime LewisOperations & Public Advocacy Advisor








×


Jaime LewisOperations & Public Advocacy Advisor
Jaime Lewis has over a decade of experience leading medical marijuana dispensary operations and managing the production of medical marijuana-infused products. Prior to joining iAnthus’ Massachusetts affiliate, Mayflower Medicinals, Jaime was the Chief Operating Officer of a large Colorado medical dispensary operation, where she was responsible for operations, strategic planning, business development, governmental affairs and community relations. She is the founder of Mountain Medicine, an infused cannabis product manufacturer and distributor to Colorado dispensaries. Jaime is a founding member of the Cannabis Business Alliance, an influential trade organization that functions as the Colorado industry’s chamber of commerce, and the Chairwoman of the Board of Directors of the National Cannabis Industry Association, where she serves as a national spokesperson for the regulated cannabis industry. Prior to entering the cannabis industry, Jaime was the executive chef of a Michelin-rated restaurant in San Francisco.
 









Mr. Rosen most recently served as President and CEO of PharmaCan Capital Corporation, a publicly traded investment firm focused on investing in Canada’s medical marijuana industry.
LEARN MORE


Paul RosenFinancial Advisor








×


Paul RosenFinancial Advisor
Paul Rosen is a founder of PharmaCan Capital Corporation, a publically traded investment firm focused on investing in Canada’s medical marijuana industry, where he served as President and CEO for three years. While CEO at PharmaCan, Paul executed the successful purchase of In The Zone Produce Ltd (“ITZ”), a Canadian medical marijuana producer licensed by Health Canada, following which he concurrently served as President and the Senior Person in Charge (SPIC) at ITZ. Prior to founding PharmaCan, Paul founded and served as CEO of Skypad Inc. (“Skypad”), a leading global contract manufacturer. Paul currently serves as Skypad’s Chairman. Paul is a member of the Law Society of Upper Canada and practiced constitutional law in Canada for several years. Paul received a B.A. in Economics from Western University in 1985 and an LL.B. from the University of Toronto in 1988.










Mr. Sederberg is a founding partner of Vicente Sederberg, LLC, a leading national law firm specializing in the areas of cannabis regulation, business, and marijuana policy reform. LEARN MORE


Christian SederbergRegulatory Advisor








×


Christian SederbergRegulatory Advisor
Christian Sederberg is a partner and founding member of the Vicente Sederberg, LLC, a leading national law firm specializing in the areas of cannabis regulation, business, and marijuana policy reform. Since the inception of Colorado’s state regulated medical marijuana program, Mr. Sederberg and his firm have provided a wide range of real estate, transactional and regulatory legal expertise to licensed marijuana businesses and to Colorado and national advocacy groups. Mr. Sederberg was an integral part of Colorado’s Amendment 64 campaign, representing the campaign on Governor Hickenlooper’s Amendment 64 Implementation Task Force and coordinating the implementation of the Colorado legislative and regulatory structure related to the adult-use marijuana program. Mr. Sederberg served on the executive committee of the Committee for Responsible Regulation, which coordinated the campaign to establish statewide excise and sales taxes on the sale of adult-use marijuana in Colorado. Mr. Sederberg received his J.D. degree from the University of Colorado School of Law.









Mr. Sheperd provides strategic advisory and investments services to a range of industries.
LEARN MORE


Russell ShepardAdvisor








×


Russell ShepardAdvisor
From 2003 to 2014, Mr. Shepard was the head trader at Renaissance Technologies LLC (“Renaissance”), a highly respected quantitative investment fund that earned exceptional returns through mathematical and statistical methods. Over his 16 years at Renaissance, Mr. Shepard was instrumental in the performance of the firm’s funds which grew to over $60 billion under management. Since leaving Renaissance, Mr. Shepard has founded three successful businesses and recently founded a fourth, Pursuit Advisory LP, a strategic advisory and investment firm that provides transaction and strategic advisory services to media, technology, digital, and private equity clients, and serves as a principal investor in the media and technology sectors. Mr. Shepard serves on the Board of Directors of the East Harlem School, the Board of Trustees at the Marymount School, and on the Board of the Stony Brook University Endowment Investment Committee. Mr. Shepard is a noted philanthropist who has made substantial contributions to several other schools and organizations including the World Science Foundation, Partners in Health, The Robin Hood Foundation, and Texas Children’s Hospital. Mr. Shepard received a B.A. in Business Administration from James Madison University.









Ms. Sullivan is recognized as one of the women venture capitalists changing the world for entrepreneurs.
LEARN MORE


Jeanne M. SullivanAdvisor








×


Jeanne M. SullivanAdvisor
Jeanne M. Sullivan is a veteran venture capital investor with more than 30 years of experience in the tech industry. Ms. Sullivan was a co-founder of StarVest Partners, a New York City-based venture fund with more than $400 million under management. Ms. Sullivan is a sought-after industry speaker, leveraging her knowledge and resources in technology and now as an investor and adviser in the cannabis sector, and is a fierce advocate for cannabis legalization. Ms. Sullivan serves on the board of the NY Venture Capital Association, the Women’s Leadership Board at the Harvard Kennedy School, and serves as an Entrepreneur Fellow at Barnard College. Forbes cited Ms. Sullivan as one of the women venture capitalists changing the world for the next generation of entrepreneurs.









 
 
  
 
 



































